The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for non-intrusive load monitoring (NILM), which involves the application of machine learning techniques to recover source appliances from recorded mains in a household. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, and this could potentially fall under the sub-category of transfer learning (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for sequence-to-point learning, which is a specific type of neural network architecture, and this could fall under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
